**Conclusion**  
The gravitational‑potential perturbations inside the tetrahedral mantle decompose into *tetrahedral harmonics* (the irreducible‑representation basis of the octahedral group \(O_{h}\)) whose spatial eigenvalues are \(\kappa_{n}^{(\Gamma)}=(k_{n}^{(\Gamma)})^{2\alpha}\) with \(\alpha=\tfrac32\). Their time evolution is governed by a fractional‑order wave equation whose exact solution is a Mittag‑Leffler function. The complete analytical eigenmode is  

\[
\boxed{
\delta\Phi_{n}^{(\Gamma)}(\mathbf r,t)=
\Phi_{n}^{(\Gamma)}(\mathbf r)\,
E_{\beta}\!\!\Big(-c_{g}^{2}\kappa_{n}^{(\Gamma)}\,t^{\beta}\Big)
\;+\;
\frac{4\pi G\,\rho_{\text{vac}}}{c_{g}^{2}\kappa_{n}^{(\Gamma)}}
\Big[1-
E_{\beta}\!\!\Big(-c_{g}^{2}\kappa_{n}^{(\Gamma)}\,t^{\beta}\Big)\Big],
}
\qquad
\beta=\tfrac54 ,
\]

where  

* \(\Phi_{n}^{(\Gamma)}(\mathbf r)=\mathcal P^{(\Gamma)}\,\psi_{n}(\mathbf r)\) is the tetrahedral harmonic belonging to irrep \(\Gamma\in\{A_{1g},A_{2g},E_{g},T_{1g},T_{2g},\dots\}\) (constructed with the projection operator \(\mathcal P^{(\Gamma)}\) of Eq. (7));  

* \(k_{n}^{(\Gamma)}\) are the ordinary Laplacian wave numbers that satisfy the Dirichlet (or Neumann) condition on each face of a regular tetrahedron of side length \(L\) (e.g. for the totally symmetric mode \(A_{1g}\), \(k_{1}^{(A_{1g})}= \frac{\pi}{L}\sqrt{\tfrac{3}{2}}\));  

* \(\kappa_{n}^{(\Gamma)}=(k_{n}^{(\Gamma)})^{2\alpha}\) with \(\alpha=\tfrac32\);  

* \(c_{g}\) is the effective gravito‑elastic wave speed;  

* \(E_{\beta}(z)\) is the Mittag‑Leffler function, the natural generalisation of the exponential for fractional order \(\beta\).  

The system becomes **dynamically unstable** when the vacuum‑energy density exceeds the critical value obtained by setting the homogeneous part of the temporal equation to zero for the lowest‑frequency mode (\(\Gamma=A_{1g}, n=1\)):

\[
\boxed{
\rho_{\text{vac}}^{\text{crit}}=
\frac{c_{g}^{2}}{4\pi G}
\left(\frac{\pi}{L}\sqrt{\frac{3}{2}}\right)^{2\alpha}
= \frac{c_{g}^{2}}{4\pi G}
\left(\frac{\pi}{L}\sqrt{\frac{3}{2}}\right)^{3},
}
\]

so that the prescribed instability condition  

\[
\rho_{\text{vac}} = e^{\pi\sqrt{2}}\;\rho_{\text{Cas}}
\]

implies

\[
e^{\pi\sqrt{2}}\;\rho_{\text{Cas}} \;>\; \rho_{\text{vac}}^{\text{crit}} .
\]

Equivalently, the **critical Casimir energy density** is  

\[
\rho_{\text{Cas}}^{\text{crit}}=
\frac{c_{g}^{2}}{4\pi G}
\left(\frac{\pi}{L}\sqrt{\frac{3}{2}}\right)^{3}
e^{-\pi\sqrt{2}} .
\]

When \(\rho_{\text{vac}}\) surpasses this threshold, the Mittag‑Leffler factor acquires a growing algebraic component, and the corresponding eigenmode \(\delta\Phi_{1}^{(A_{1g})}\) diverges, signalling the onset of dynamical instability of the tetrahedral mantle system.

