Let $ G $ be a finitely generated group of polynomial growth, and let $ \mathcal{G} = \lim_{r \to \infty} \frac{\log \left| B_G(r) \right|}{\log r} $ denote the growth rate exponent, where $ B_G(r) $ is the ball of radius $ r $ in the Cayley graph of $ G $. Suppose $ G $ admits a nilpotent subgroup $ N \trianglelefteq G $ of finite index, and let $ \mathfrak{n} $ be the associated nilpotent Lie algebra of $ N $. Consider the space $ \mathcal{H}^1(G, \mathbb{R}) $ of real-valued 1-cocycles on $ G $ modulo 1-coboundaries, equipped with the natural topology induced by the uniform convergence on compact sets. Prove that the following are equivalent:

(i) The group $ G $ is virtually abelian and $ \mathcal{G} \in \mathbb{N} $;  
(ii) The space $ \mathcal{H}^1(G, \mathbb{R}) $ is finite-dimensional and the action of $ G $ on $ \mathcal{H}^1(G, \mathbb{R}) $ via the adjoint representation on $ \mathfrak{n} $ extends to a continuous linear action on the associated Carnot–Carathéodory metric space $ (\mathfrak{n}, d_{\text{CC}}) $;  
(iii) There exists a nilpotent Lie group $ \mathbf{N} $ with Lie algebra $ \mathfrak{n} $, and a lattice $ \Gamma \subset \mathbf{N} $, such that the quotient $ \mathbf{N}/\Gamma $ admits a smooth, $ G $-invariant Riemannian metric whose volume growth is asymptotic to $ r^{\mathcal{G}} $, and the induced action of $ G $ on $ \mathbf{N}/\Gamma $ is isometric and ergodic with respect to the normalized Haar measure.

Furthermore, construct an explicit example of such a group $ G $ with $ \mathcal{G} = 7 $, where $ \mathfrak{n} $ has step 3 and dimension 15, and verify that the associated Carnot group $ \mathbf{N} $ satisfies the above properties, using the full machinery of Gromov's theorem, the structure theory of nilpotent Lie algebras, and the metric geometry of sub-Riemannian manifolds.

